review.body: Thank you very much for this PR -- and particularly the OpenSSL3 integration: It works like a charm! Also Thanks for the script to trigger all algorithms (and the various Segmentation faults as per the discussion). I'd be fine to merge this as-is -- only tiny improvement suggestion: Would it be reasonable to extend the list of algorithms in "check_algorithms.sh" with the hybrid variants? Please let us know whether you'd like to update this before merge.

pull_request.body:
Hi, I integrated openssl v3 and oqs-provider into h2load benchmarking tool and provided a Dockerfile to fully automate the integration.

Thanks for reviewing!

review.body:
> It turns out the build was failing due to changes in the library versions. It builds properly now that I have addressed this by using wildcards. Once again thank you for your valuable input!

Thank you for the update! Everything now indeed builds OK. However, the CI test (still) fails (see command sequence above): For one, the new docker image doesn't contain bash, but secondly, no (test) CA is "baked into" the image: How would you recommend to change things to have a good CI test for this PR?
